          <source>How to: Resize Controls on Windows Forms</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can resize individual controls, and you can resize multiple controls of the same or different kind, such as <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button&gt;</ph> and <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.GroupBox&gt;</ph> controls.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To resize a control</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click the control to be resized and drag one of the eight sizing handles.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select the control and press the ARROW keys while holding down the SHIFT key to resize the control one pixel at a time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Press the DOWN or RIGHT arrow keys while holding down the SHIFT and CTRL keys to resize the control in large increments.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To resize multiple controls on a form</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Hold down the CTRL or SHIFT key and select the controls you want to resize.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The size of the first control you select is used for the other controls.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Format<ept id="p1">**</ept> menu, choose <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Make Same Size<ept id="p2">**</ept>, and select one of the four options.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The first three commands change the dimensions of the controls to match the first-selected control.</source>
        </trans-unit>
